name: Kober Dalung

review 1:

Kober noodles is famous with inexpensive but delicious meal.

Consistent food quality and affordable.

Always yummy and well affordable for pocket. Kids and young people love this place.
review 2: The place was so strategic because it's near the housing, the university, and some high schools. The parking space was wide enough. We need to queue to order the food and beverage. name: Tri Hita Vegan
address: Jl. Tibung Sari No.58, Dalung, Kec. Kuta Utara, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80117, Indonesia
review 1:
Banging. The food is delicious! We drove 30 minutes for this food and ate here two days in a row. It has been up there with the best Balinese/Indonesian food we have eaten over the past 4 weeks. It has been the best Nasi Campur we have tried. We also loved the koloke!! All the dishes we had were delicious and EVERYTHING is vegan and so many options.

The staff are super friendly and welcoming, there‚Äôs no fuss in terms of decor but it is a nice place to sit and enjoy.

The food is very cheap.

If we had found this place sooner I‚Äôm sure we would of ate here many more times.

We highly recommend üôå
review 2: Best food for the best price. Only 15k for nasi campur of your option with free soup?! And only 5k for coconut drinks. Preferable for breakfast, their menu is even complete in the morning.
review 3:
The food here was all vegan and delicious. It is usually hard to find diversity of vegetarian/ vegan Indonesian food. However, this place has veganised many Indonesian dishes and it was lovely to taste the flavours!

There is also a fruit seller next doors who helped us understand the menu since he spoke English. We also bought the most delicious mangoes from him.
review 4: If you managed to discover this place, then congratulations, you just found a good vegetarian restaurant to eat. Their sidedish portion is so big that I need add rice to match the sidedish and the taste was like freshly made and flavorful. Looking forward to come here again.
review 5:
The staff are super friendly and helpful, place is quite clean, and the food is tasty.

I've been here many times, but funny thing is that I've *never* seen the menu...

One time, I showed up quite late, and I was stuck with the limited buffet (leftover at end of the day). I wasn't expecting it but they gave me a discount which is a really nice gesture.

name: Mr.Takoyaki Dalung
address: Jl. Raya Padang Luwih No.110, Dalung, Kec. Kuta Utara, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
If you're looking for a delicious and affordable takoyaki in Dalung, then you need to check out Mr. Takoyaki Dalung. This small street food stall is a popular spot for locals and tourists alike, and it's serving up some of the best takoyaki in town.

The service at Mr. Takoyaki Dalung is also excellent. The staff is friendly and attentive, and they're always happy to make recommendations.

Overall, Mr. Takoyaki Dalung is a great place to go for a delicious and affordable Japanese street food meal. The food is excellent, the service is great, and the prices are very reasonable. I highly recommend it!

Here are some additional details that you may want to include in your review:

Mr. Takoyaki Dalung is located in Jl. Raya Padang Luwih No.110, Dalung, Kuta Utara, Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia.
The hours of operation are 10:45 am to 10:00 pm, every day.
The prices are very reasonable. A plate of takoyaki costs around Rp20,000.
Mr. Takoyaki Dalung is a very popular spot, so it can get crowded during peak hours. If you're planning on visiting, it's best to go early or late in the day.
I highly recommend Mr. Takoyaki Dalung to anyone looking for a delicious and affordable Japanese street food meal. It's a great place to try takoyaki for the first time, or to enjoy a quick and tasty snack.
